4. Selected optimization:
The most impactful optimization would be to replace the unordered_set with a vector + sort + unique approach for storing primary key IDs. This is because:
- We're inserting many elements (potentially thousands)
- unordered_set has higher memory overhead and slower insertion times
- We don't need the set properties during insertion, only at the end
- The final iteration will be just as fast with a vector
- This matches patterns seen in other high-performance spatial databases

